Example project with Flask and Redis running with Docker.

Featuring:
 - Docker
 - Docker Compose
 - Docker Machine
 - Python 3.5
 - Flask
 - Redis

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
OS X Instructions
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

If you don't already have Docker on OS X: https://docs.docker.com/engine/installation/mac/#/docker-toolbox

For Redis Master Instance
* Inside `redis-master` directory *
1. Start new machine (`$ docker-machine -d virtualbox redis-master`)
2. Build images (`$ docker-compose build`)
3. Start services (`$ docker-compose up`)

For Redis Slave Instance
* Inside `redis-slave` directory *
1. Start new machine (`$ docker-machine -d virtualbox redis-slave`)
2. Build images (`$ docker-compose build`)
3. Start services (`$ docker-compose up`)

For the Flask app

1. Start new machine (`$ docker-machine -d virtualbox flask-app`)
2. Build images (`$ docker-compose build`)
3. Start services (`$ docker-compose up`)
4. Grab IP (`$ docker-machine ip flask-app`) and view in your browser
